    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Kunming</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lutkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kunming</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-07"> November 7,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received November 7—1:55 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>220. Acting President Li in address November 5 called on Yunnanese people to
                    re-enact their traditional record of self-sacrificing patriotism so as to ensure
                    success of rebellion suppression and national reconstruction. Defined struggle
                    as between democracy and totalitarianism, saying Nationalist Government had
                    dedicated itself to task of preserving people’s freedom and nation’s independent
                    sovereignty. Argued struggle was one against aggression just as anti-Japanese
                    war. Admitted seriousness of situation and acknowledged faults of the <pb
                        facs="0591" n="581" xml:id="pg_581"/> Nationalist Government but professed
                    faith in ultimate victory if faith and determination retained.</p>
                <p>Sent Chungking 84, repeated Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lutkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
